.TH NYMEA-CLI 1 "March 2026" "nymea-cli 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
nymea-cli \- terminal client for nymead
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B nymea-cli
[\fB\-H\fR \fIhost\fR]
[\fB\-s\fR]
[\fB\-p\fR \fIport\fR]
[\fB\-t\fR \fIms\fR]
[\fB\-u\fR \fIusername\fR]
[\fB\-w\fR \fIpassword\fR]
[\fB\-\-help\fR]
[\fB\-\-version\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B nymea-cli
is a fullscreen terminal client for
.BR nymead .
It connects to the nymea JSON-RPC API over plain TCP or SSL/TLS and
provides a keyboard-driven interface for browsing things, inspecting
metadata, and executing actions.
.PP
The default nymea ports are 2223 for plain TCP and 2222 for SSL/TLS.
Stored authentication tokens are reused across restarts. TLS connections
store the peer certificate fingerprint and warn if it changes later.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-H ", " \-\-host " " \fIhost\fR
nymead host to connect to. The default is
.BR 127.0.0.1 .
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-ssl
Use SSL/TLS via
.BR QSslSocket .
This changes the default port to 2222.
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-port " " \fIport\fR
Connect to the given TCP port. If omitted, the default is 2222 with
.B \-\-ssl
or 2223 otherwise.
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-timeout " " \fIms\fR
Timeout in milliseconds for connection and reply waits. The default is
.BR 5000 .
.TP
.BR \-u ", " \-\-username " " \fIusername\fR
Username for JSONRPC.Authenticate.
.TP
.BR \-w ", " \-\-password " " \fIpassword\fR
Password for JSONRPC.Authenticate.
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Show command line help and exit.
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show the program version and exit.
.SH INTERFACE
Global keys:
.TP
.B q
Quit the application.
.TP
.B Esc
Quit the application or close the active dialog.
.TP
.B c
Reconnect to the configured nymea server.
.TP
.B h
Run the JSONRPC.Hello handshake again.
.TP
.B t
Refresh the thing list.
.PP
Main layout keys:
.TP
.B Up / Down
Move inside the focused list.
.TP
.B Left / Right
Switch focus between panels.
.TP
.B Space
Open or close the metadata inspector for the selected param, state, or
action.
.TP
.B Enter
Open the selected action or setup flow.
.PP
Action dialog keys:
.TP
.B Up / Down
Select the current parameter.
.TP
.B Left / Right / Space
Cycle selector values for boolean or allowed-values parameters.
.TP
.B Enter
Execute the action.
.TP
.B Esc
Close the dialog without executing.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /var/lib/nymea/nymea-cli.conf
Settings file used when running as root.
.TP
.I ~/.config/nymea/nymea-cli.conf
Settings file used for non-root users.
.PP
Saved connections are keyed by nymea host UUID and store the host,
selected port, SSL flag, authentication token, and TLS fingerprint.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Connect to a local nymea instance using plain TCP:
.IP
.EX
nymea-cli
.EE
.TP
Connect to a remote host with TLS:
.IP
.EX
nymea-cli --ssl --host nymea.example.org
.EE
.TP
Authenticate with explicit credentials:
.IP
.EX
nymea-cli --host 192.0.2.10 --username admin --password secret
.EE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Invalid command line arguments or application failure.
.SH SECURITY
Passing a password on the command line can expose it to other local users
through process listings. Prefer interactive authentication when possible.
